                <opener>
                    <hi rend="caps">NEW CALEDONIA</hi> <dateline>8 <hi rend="caps">MARCH</hi> '45</dateline>

                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute></opener> <p>Thanks so much for your warm letter. It has done me a lot of good. Guess we all tend to get a bit low in spirit now and then. At the moment, I am feeling "high hearted with a hunger for the new." Being a native Nebraskan, (an Omahan) I felt that it gave me permission to write to you. I heard you in a lecture at Omaha's Joslyn Memorial some time ago and ever since have wanted to contact you. I went through my <unclear>basic</unclear> training with a Pete Grayhair grandson of a Winnebego chief. He was most interesting and I hope to renew our friendship when this war is all finished. This island its history and its people, is very interesting. Hope we can have a good long talk some day. Thanks again for your kindness in writing <unclear>to me</unclear></p> <closer><salute>Sincerely</salute> <signed>Bob Hyde</signed></closer>
                
